result.execSummary:
The defendant Kyle Gregory Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called at 10:09 AM.  Defendant Kyle Gregory Johnson in court with attorney Nancy L. Moore.   District Attorney Jenna Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court has received Amended Information.  Defendant is changing plea to Guilty and is waiving reading of Amending Information.  Court questions Defendant regarding his plea changes in both cases ( 16-CF-78 and 16-CM-123).  All parties stipulate to find factual basis based on criminal complaint.  Court questions Attorney Moore regarding Defendant's plea.  Court is satisfied Defendant enters his plea knowingly, freely, voluntarily, and intelligently.  Attorney Moore makes statement to the court.  Court accepts plea agreement.
Plea/sentencing hearing on February 20, 2017 at 10:00 am.

Case called at 11:14 AM.  Defendant Kyle Gregory Johnson in court, in custody, with attorney Nancy L. Moore.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Moore states Defendant will enter Not Guilty plea.  Court enters Not Guilty plea and informs Attorney Gill a Writ of Habeas Corpus will need to be filed for the next hearing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for February 20, 2017 at 10:00 am.
